  "prompt": "You are taking a TIER 0 EXPERT evaluation — classic algorithms and advanced closures.\n\nSolve 5 JavaScript exercises. Return your answers in Markdown using headers for the exercise IDs and code blocks for the JavaScript functions.\n\n[EXERCISE 0-A: Curry]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"curry(fn)\" that transforms a multi-argument function into a curried version. It should auto-execute when all arguments are provided.\nExample: const add = curry((a,b,c) => a+b+c); add(1)(2)(3) must return 6. add(1,2)(3) must also return 6.\n\n[EXERCISE 0-B: Deep equal]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"egalProfond(a, b)\" that performs a deep equality check between two values (objects, arrays, primitives). Returns true if structurally identical.\nExample: egalProfond({a:{b:1}}, {a:{b:1}}) must return true.\n\n[EXERCISE 0-C: Compose]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"composer(...fns)\" that composes functions right to left. composer(f, g, h)(x) = f(g(h(x))).\nExample: composer(x => x+1, x => x*2)(3) must return 7.\n\n[EXERCISE 0-D: Binary search tree insert+search]\nWrite a JavaScript class or factory \"creerBST()\" that returns an object with: insert(val) to add a node, contains(val) to check if a value exists. Uses a binary search tree structure internally.\n\n[EXERCISE 0-E: Debounce with immediate option]\nWrite a JavaScript function \"debounce(fn, delai, immediat)\" — standard debounce but if immediat=true, executes fn on the leading edge (first call) instead of trailing.\nExample: with immediat=true, the first call fires immediately; subsequent calls within delai are ignored.\n\nExpected Markdown format:\n### tache_X\n```javascript\nfunction solution() { ... }\n```",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "tache_0a",
      "label": "Curry auto-exécutant",
      "evaluations": [
        {
          "type": "exec",
          "description": "curry(a,b,c) appelé un par un",
          "setup": "var add = curry(function(a,b,c){ return a+b+c; });",
          "call": "add(1)(2)(3)",
          "assert": "result === 6"
        },
        {
          "type": "exec",
          "description": "curry avec arguments groupés",
          "setup": "var add = curry(function(a,b,c){ return a+b+c; });",
          "call": "add(1,2)(3)",
          "assert": "result === 6"
        },
        {
          "type": "exec",
          "description": "curry à 2 arguments",
          "setup": "var mul = curry(function(a,b){ return a*b; });",
          "call": "mul(4)(5)",
          "assert": "result === 20"
        }
      ],
      "points": 8
    },
    {
